			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2023</a> paper:</span><br><i>Seamless Code Generator Synchronization in the Composition of Heterogeneous Modeling Languages</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/NicoJansen.html">Nico Jansen</a>, <a href="../profile/BernhardRumpe.html">Bernhard Rumpe</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3623476.3623530">10.1145/3623476.3623530</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagM">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> The paper addresses composition of heterogeneous modeling languages, focusing on synchronizing their code generators and artefacts.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagL">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> Code generator synchronization is fundamentally about coordinating generative/compilation pipelines across composed languages.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The solution is positioned as practical infrastructure for language/tool engineering rather than a one-off implementation.
</li></ul></li></ul>
